Title: Exploring Cancer, the Dimmest Zodiac Constellation

Summary: Despite being the dimmest constellation, Cancer holds the Beehive Cluster and stars with orbiting planets. Associated with Greek mythology, Cancer is visible in both hemispheres and contains various observation targets like Messier 67 and NGC 2775. Cancer's exoplanets orbit 55 Cancri A, and the constellation represents a giant crab in astrology.